00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:15,291
remain deeply committed to compassion

439
00:19:15,291 --> 00:19:17,000
peace and non harming

440
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:20,000
what we're examining here is how any tradition

441
00:19:20,083 --> 00:19:21,541
no matter how peaceful

442
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:24,208
can be distorted when it becomes fused with fear

443
00:19:24,416 --> 00:19:26,500
power or nationalism

444
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,208
let's start with Myanmar

445
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:32,166
where nationalist Buddhist monks led by Ashin Wirathu

446
00:19:32,166 --> 00:19:34,458
have fueled violence against Rohingya Muslims

447
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:35,916
Wirathu

448
00:19:35,916 --> 00:19:39,416
once called the Buddhist bin Laden by time magazine

449
00:19:39,833 --> 00:19:43,583
