00:22:04,416 --> 00:22:05,500
the Buddha's teachings

508
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:08,000
included a built in solution to such distortions

509
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:10,750
the practice of meditation itself

510
00:22:11,083 --> 00:22:13,791
which creates internal conditions for peace

511
00:22:18,541 --> 00:22:20,458
while other religions pray for peace

512
00:22:20,916 --> 00:22:22,583
Buddhists train their minds for it

513
00:22:22,583 --> 00:22:24,375
this isn't just spiritual talk

514
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:27,291
it's practical psychology backed by modern science

515
00:22:27,541 --> 00:22:30,958
at Buddhism's core lies a simple but profound insight

516
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:35,500
violence begins in the mind with thoughts of anger

517
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:40,125
hatred and division so peace must begin there too

518
00:22:40,541 --> 00:22:41,958
in the Buddha's words

519
00:22:42,125 --> 00:22:44,416
all that we are arises with our thoughts

520
00:22:44,791 --> 00:22:47,375
with our thoughts we make the world

521
00:22:48,583 --> 00:22:50,916
let's try a brief experiment right now

522
00:22:51,208 --> 00:22:53,916
just for 20 seconds notice your breathing

523
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:55,875
feel the sensation of air

524
00:22:55,875 --> 00:22:57,666
