525
00:22:58,166 --> 00:22:59,500
when your mind wanders

526
00:22:59,500 --> 00:23:02,166
and it will gently bring it back to your breath

527
00:23:15,416 --> 00:23:16,333
that pause

528
00:23:17,166 --> 00:23:21,583
that was a seed of peace in that space no war can grow

529
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:24,750
what you just experienced

530
00:23:24,750 --> 00:23:26,958
is the foundation of Buddhist meditation

531
00:23:27,166 --> 00:23:29,500
creating awareness of your mental processes

532
00:23:30,083 --> 00:23:30,791
now imagine

533
00:23:30,791 --> 00:23:33,708
extending this ability to moments when anger arises

534
00:23:34,166 --> 00:23:37,375
