00:23:48,833 --> 00:23:51,291
directly addresses the root causes of aggression

543
00:23:51,625 --> 00:23:53,750
it doesn't just tell you to be peaceful

544
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,333
it trains your brain to

545
00:23:55,333 --> 00:23:57,000
respond differently to provocations

546
00:23:57,625 --> 00:24:00,333
modern neuroscience echoes what monks intuited

547
00:24:00,333 --> 00:24:01,541
centuries ago

548
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:04,333
regular meditation physically changes the brain

549
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:05,875
in ways that reduce aggression

550
00:24:06,708 --> 00:24:09,250
neuroscientists at the university of Wisconsin

551
00:24:09,250 --> 00:24:12,041
measured brain activity in experienced meditators

552
00:24:12,625 --> 00:24:14,291
they found increased activity

553
00:24:14,291 --> 00:24:17,000
in areas associated with positive emotions

554
00:24:17,208 --> 00:24:20,000
and reduced activity in aggression related areas

555
00:24:20,666 --> 00:24:24,166
even in war zones meditation creates islands of peace

556
00:24:24,583 --> 00:24:26,833
during Cambodia's bloody civil war

557
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:28,458
monk Maha Ghosananda

